benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to invoice item

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05 cover successful modifications with required and optional headers, including cases with no prior custom fields and existing custom fields.
Non-Existing Resource: @TC07 covers attempt to modify a non-existent invoice item with 404 response.

Invalid Input: @TC06 covers invalid invoiceItemId format; @TC08 covers malformed JSON body; @TC09 covers missing required header; @TC10 covers empty request body; @TC11 covers unsupported fields; @TC14 covers SQL injection payloads.
Security & Authorization: @TC09, @TC14, @TC13 (invalid auth) cover missing or invalid authentication and security concerns.
Error Handling: @TC06, @TC08, @TC09, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC19, @TC24, @TC25 cover various error scenarios including server errors, timeouts, and database unavailability.
Idempotency & Regression: @TC17, @TC18 verify repeated requests and regression fixes.
Performance & Load: @TC20, @TC21 cover large payloads, parallel requests, and performance thresholds.
Edge Cases: @TC22, @TC23 test minimum/maximum values and URL parameters.
State Variations: @TC24, @TC25 test empty and partially populated database states.
Dependent Service & External Failures: @TC19 covers external service unavailability.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized users beyond missing headers; no role-based access control scenarios.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Concurrency & Race Conditions: No explicit tests for concurrent modifications or race conditions.
Timeouts & System Load: No specific tests simulate system under heavy load or network delays beyond @TC16.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large datasets and pagination headers.
Include explicit authorization tests for different user roles and unauthorized access attempts.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under high request volumes.
Create scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Develop concurrency tests to check for race conditions during simultaneous updates.
Simulate network delays and timeouts to verify system robustness under load.
